# Docker build context excludes (spec 11, T10 follow-up).
# Without this, the persona-api build context bloats to ~1 GB because
# .venv (with torch + sentence-transformers wheels) and node_modules
# are copied into the daemon. After this file: < 5 MB context, ~5×
# faster builds.

# Python venv + caches
.venv/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/
**/coverage*
**/htmlcov/

# Web (large)
packages/web/node_modules/
packages/web/.next/
packages/web/.turbo/
packages/web/test-results/
packages/web/playwright-report/

# Secrets — never bake into the image (set via flyctl secrets instead)
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
packages/api/.secrets/
packages/web/.env.local
deploy/.env.production

# Build/release artifacts
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/

# Git / tooling
.git/
.github/
.idea/
.vscode/
**/.DS_Store

# Docs are not needed by the runtime image
docs/
CHANGELOG.md
LAUNCH_CHECKLIST.md
README.md
**/*.md
# Re-include the bundled SKILL.md files + their supplements (architecture
# §9.3, spec 13/16). These are package data the SkillScanner reads at
# runtime via ``<base>/<name>/SKILL.md``; the broad ``**/*.md`` rule above
# would strip them by default → /v1/skills returns empty → the authoring
# wizard can't suggest any skill. Mirrors ``packages/core/pyproject.toml``
# hatchling include = ["src/persona/skills/builtin/**/SKILL.md", ...].
!packages/core/src/persona/skills/builtin/**/SKILL.md
!packages/core/src/persona/skills/builtin/**/supplements/*.md

# Re-include per-package README.md files (v0.2 OSS prep). Each package's
# pyproject.toml declares ``readme = "README.md"``; without these, hatchling
# fails ``uv sync`` during the builder stage with
# ``OSError: Readme file does not exist: README.md`` when validating package
# metadata. Mirrors the SKILL.md re-include pattern above.
!packages/core/README.md
!packages/runtime/README.md
!packages/api/README.md
!packages/voice/README.md

# Tests are not needed by the runtime image
packages/*/tests/
